\text{Total Asset Turnover Ratio} = \frac{\text{Total Revenue}}{\text{Average Total Assets}}

- Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 14,214,117.02) / 2 = 13,607,058.51

**Step 3: Calculate Ratio**
- Total Asset Turnover Ratio = 2,637,011.03 / 13,607,058.51 â‰ˆ 0.194
